9: Well! At least I've stopped fainting.
12:
That's just 'cause you've built up a
tolerance to poison.
16:
Nimbus. You've come to laugh at
me, haven't you?
20:
Oh, I'm laughin'. But I'm HERE for a
non-toxic snack.
24:
You are a human with opposable
thumbs.
27:
Thus, you are physically capable of
cooking. Good luck.
35:
If you wanna get good fast, ask Alk
to teach you. You're gonna die of old
age or food poisonin' at this rate.
38: Alk has enough chores to do.
40:
If nothing else, I have learned that
work in the kitchen never ends...
43:
Oh yeah. You're washing the dishes
now, right? Alk said it's taken a load
off his shoulders.
46:
That's because I don't want to stand
in his debt. Those who lean on
others never learn to walk on their
own.
49: Funny words, comin' from a rich kid.
53:
You're right... All my life, I have lived
in the lap of luxury.
56:
I thought the world was simple, but
that was only because I didn't
realize how privileged I was... I am
the worst kind of fool.
62:
That's why I need to do this... on my
own.
69:
Urgh... My head... and stomach...
hurt... But there is still shopping that
needs... to get done...
74:
You're as big a blockhead as always,
Yuwel!
79:
What an eye-opener... I've heard
stories about Starview, but nothing
beats seeing the real thing.
80:
You've chosen quite a place for your
new home.
83:
I can't believe it! I'm in a different
world! If only the rest of the Knights
were here!
86: Quiet, Will. You're acting like a child.
88:
Now tell me... Why did you come to
Starview all of a sudden?
91:
Can't I want to visit an old friend "all
of a sudden"? Or did you not want to
see me?
96:
Stella told me everything. Yuwel, an
aspiring chef! The other Knights
would laugh themselves blue in the
face if they found out.
98:
I'd ask you back to the Farlands, but
I know you won't come.
101:
Yes, Will... I am on a journey, which is
still far from being over.
103:
There aren't any more monster
attacks back home, you know. The
duty of the Swallow Knights has
been fulfilled... Though, I admit, that's
no thanks to us.
106:
But there are still people who need
help outside of the Farlands. It isn't
yet time for me to lay down my
sword.
109:
You really haven't changed, have
you? Guess it's just me who's
become more of a realist these past
three years.
111:
Well, I hope everything works out for
you. You've got yourself some
dependable friends this time around.
116:
I never could have made it out of
the Farlands alone. Likely would
have poisoned myself to death by
the third day.
122:
And, Will, it seems that I am in need
of your help again.
127:
Well, that, my friend, is not as simple
as it seems.
131:
Hey, you're back. That was faster
than expected.
139: Thank you, Stella... For talking to Will.
141:
And Alk. I'm afraid I must ask you for
the favor of a lifetime...
143:
Will you teach me how to make that
most confounding stew, zoni?
147:
...What?
I-I mean, that's fine but... Not exactly
what I'd call "a favor of a lifetime."
150: Thank you. I am in your debt.
153:
A debt that shall, WITHOUT A DOUBT,
be repaid. Is that clear? I WILL NOT
FORGET THIS.
